lgrims who had travelled to Israel and Egypt, as well as their contacts.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.cnn.gr/news/ellada/story/210074/koronoios-stin-ellada-sta-31-ta-kroysmata-toy-ioy-21-nea |title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1: \u03a3\u03c4\u03b1 31 \u03c4\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1 \u2013 21 \u03bd\u03ad\u03b1 |last=Newsroom |date=2020-03-05 |website=CNN.gr |language=el |access-date=2020-03-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323114331/https://www.cnn.gr/news/ellada/story/210074/koronoios-stin-ellada-sta-31-ta-kroysmata-toy-ioy-21-nea |archive-date=23 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.newsit.gr/ellada/koronoios-14-akoma-krousmata-stin-ellad/2988717/ |title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: 14 \u03b1\u03ba\u03cc\u03bc\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1! |website=www.newsit.gr |url-status=live |access-date=2020-03-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307063741/https://www.newsit.gr/ellada/koronoios-14-akoma-krousmata-stin-ellad/2988717/ |archive-date=7 March 2020 }}</ref> Health and state authorities issued precautionary guidelines and recommendations, while measures up to that point were taken locally and included the closure of schools and the suspension of cultural events in the affected areas (particularly [[Elis (regional unit)|Ilia]], [[Achaea]] and [[Zakynthos]]).<ref name=\":0\" /> The first confirmed death from COVID-19 in Greece was a 66-year-old man, who died on 12 March.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/greece-reports-first-coronavirus-death-66-year-old-man/ |title=Greece reports first coronavirus death, 66-year-old man |date=12 March 2020 |website=straitstimes.com |access-date=13 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.o