{"title_page": "Maldici\u00f3n (song)", "text_new": "{{short description|2019 song by Lola Indigo and Lalo Ebratt}}\n\n{{Infobox song|name=Maldici\u00f3n|cover=LolaIndigoMaldici\u00f3n.jpeg|alt=|type=single|artist=[[Lola Indigo]] and [[Lalo Ebratt]]|album=[[Akelarre (Lola Indigo album)|Akelarre]]|language=Spanish|English_title=\"Curse\"|released=April 26, 2019|format={{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[Streaming media|streaming]]}}|recorded=2018|studio=|genre=[[Pop music|Pop trap]]|length={{duration|m=3|s=8}}|label=[[Universal Music Group|Universal Music]]|writer={{hlist|Eduardo Mario Ebratt|Felipe Gonz\u00e1lez Abad|Miguel \u00c1ngel Ospino|Miriam Doblas Mu\u00f1oz}}|producer=Yera \u00b7 Nab\u00e1lez|chronology=[[Lola Indigo]]|prev_title=[[Mujer bruja|Mujer Bruja]]|prev_year=2018|next_title=[[Me quedo|Me Quedo]]|next_year=2019|misc={{Extra chronology|artist=[[Lalo Ebratt]]|type=single|prev_title=No Todav\u00eda|prev_year=2019|title=Maldici\u00f3n|year=2019|next_title=Andan Diciendo|next_year=2019}}}}\"'''Maldici\u00f3n'''\" (Spanish for \"Curse\") is a song recorded by Spanish singer [[Lola \u00cdndigo|Lola Indigo]] in collaboration with Colombian rapper [[Lalo Ebratt]]. The track was released on April 26, 2019 though [[Universal Music Group|Universal Music Spain]] as the third and final single of Indigo's debut studio album \"''[[Akelarre (Lola Indigo album)|Akelarre]]''\" (2019). \"Maldici\u00f3n\" peaked at number 21 on the [[Productores de M\u00fasica de Espa\u00f1a|PROMUSICAE]] chart and is certified gold in Spain for selling over 20,000 copies.<ref>{{Citation|last=M\u00fasica|first=El portal de|title=Maldici\u00f3n - Lola Indigo x Lalo Ebratt {{!}} EPDM|url=https://www.elportaldemusica.es/single/lola-indigo-x-lalo-ebratt-maldicion|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref> The single also charted in Colombia at number 80, marking the first single of Indigo to enter a musical chart outside Spain.\n\n== Background ==\nAfter releasing her second single \"Mujer Bruja\", Indigo began teasing her debut studio album and revealed that it would have a concept focused in witchery. On March 15, 2019, she announced that \"Akelarre\" would be released in April which didn't happen because of multiple delays due to disagreements with the record label. Through her respective social networks, Lola Indigo announced on April 20 that the third single from her new album \"Maldici\u00f3n\", in collaboration with Colombian rapper Lalo Ebratt, would be released on April 26 of that same year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vinilonegro.com/2019/04/lola-indigo-da-comienzo-la-cuenta-atras-para-akelarre-con-su-nueva-cancion-maldicion-que-se-lanza-el-26-de-abril/|title=Lola Indigo da comienzo la cuenta atr\u00e1s para \u2018Akelarre\u2019, con su nueva canci\u00f3n \u2018Maldici\u00f3n\u2019, que se lanza el 26 de abril|date=2019-04-19|website=Vinilo Negro|language=es|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref> \n\n== Music video ==\nThe music video for \"Maldici\u00f3n\" was released on April 26 and features both singers and multiple dancers jamming to the song. The videoclip features some dark scenarios, a recreation of Lucifer's throne and also shows Indigo blending the appearance of ''[[The Birth of Venus]]'' as painted by [[Sandro Botticelli]] in the 1480s decade.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cosmopolitan.com/es/famosos/musica/a27279716/lola-indigo-maldicion-nueva-cancion/|title=Nos hemos vuelto completamente 'malas' al escuchar la nueva canci\u00f3n de Lola Indigo: 'Maldici\u00f3n'|last=Panicello|first=Por Nerea|date=2019-04-26|website=Cosmopolitan|language=es-ES|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref> The music video received over one milion views in its first 24 hours and was the most-bought music video on ITunes Spain for a small amount of hours.\n\n== Live performances ==\nIndigo performed \"Maldici\u00f3n\" for the first time as part of her \"Indigo Tour\" on April 27, 2019, when she performed at the Dance Park Festival in Torrej\u00f3n de Ardoz. Indigo also performed the single and on other several festivals as well as on her Akelarre Tour, which run from May to November 2019 and is set to begin a festival extension in June 2020. The song was first performed on live television on May 16 at ''[[El Hormiguero]]'', Spain's main and most-watched late night show.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.antena3.com/programas/el-hormiguero/invitados/lola-indigo-y-su-ultimo-single-maldicion-cautivan-el-plato_201905165cddc8560cf27d3dafd39cc3.html|title=Lola \u00cdndigo y su \u00faltimo single 'Maldici\u00f3n' cautivan el plat\u00f3 de 'El Hormiguero 3.0'|date=2019-05-16|website=Antena3|language=es|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref> Indigo also sang the track at the [[Los 40|Los40 Primavera Pop]] shows in Barcelona and Madrid, with the last one being aired on ''[[Divinity (TV channel)|Divinity]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://los40.com/los40/2019/05/17/videos/1558117704_685276.html|title=Lola \u00cdndigo hace rugir al p\u00fablico con su actuaci\u00f3n en LOS40 Primavera Pop|last=LOS40|date=2019-05-18|website=LOS40|language=es|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n\n== Charts ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! scope=\"col\" |Chart (2019)\n! scope=\"col\" |Peak<br />position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |Spain ([[Productores de M\u00fasica de Espa\u00f1a|PROMUSICAE]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.elportaldemusica.es/lists/top-100-canciones/2019/18|title=El portal de M\u00fasica|website=www.elportaldemusica.es|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n|21\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |Colombia ([[National-Report]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190523143603/http://www.national-report.com/top-colombia/|title=Top 100 Colombia - national-REPORT|date=2019-05-23|website=web.archive.org|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n|80\n|}\n\n== Certifications ==\n{{Certification Table Top}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Spain|artist=Lola Indigo|title=Maldici\u00f3n|award=Gold|type=single|relyear=2019|certyear=2019|id=lola-indigo-lalo-ebratt-maldici\u00f3n|accessdate=14 April 2020}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom|nosales=true}}\n\n== Release history ==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n!Country\n!Date\n!Format\n!Label\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |Various\n|April 26, 2019\n|{{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[Streaming media|streaming]]}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Universal Music]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |Spain\n|April 28, 2019\n|[[Contemporary hit radio]]\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2019 singles]]\n[[Category:2019 songs]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2019 song by Lola Indigo and Lalo Ebratt}}\n\n{{Infobox song|name=Maldici\u00f3n|cover=LolaIndigoMaldici\u00f3n.jpeg|alt=|type=single|artist=[[Lola Indigo]] and [[Lalo Ebratt]]|album=[[Akelarre (Lola Indigo album)|Akelarre]]|language=Spanish|English_title=\"Curse\"|released=April 26, 2019|format={{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[Streaming media|streaming]]}}|recorded=2018|studio=|genre=[[Pop music|Pop trap]]|length={{duration|m=3|s=8}}|label=[[Universal Music Group|Universal Music]]|writer={{hlist|Eduardo Mario Ebratt|Felipe Gonz\u00e1lez Abad|Miguel \u00c1ngel Ospino|Miriam Doblas Mu\u00f1oz}}|producer=Yera \u00b7 Nab\u00e1lez|chronology=[[Lola Indigo]]|prev_title=[[Mujer bruja|Mujer Bruja]]|prev_year=2018|next_title=[[Me quedo|Me Quedo]]|next_year=2019|misc={{Extra chronology|artist=[[Lalo Ebratt]]|type=single|prev_title=No Todav\u00eda|prev_year=2019|title=Maldici\u00f3n|year=2019|next_title=Andan Diciendo|next_year=2019}}}}\"'''Maldici\u00f3n'''\" (Spanish for \"Curse\") is a song recorded by Spanish singer [[Lola \u00cdndigo|Lola Indigo]] in collaboration with Colombian rapper [[Lalo Ebratt]]. The track was released on April 26, 2019 though [[Universal Music Group|Universal Music Spain]] as the third and final single of Indigo's debut studio album \"''[[Akelarre (Lola Indigo album)|Akelarre]]''\" (2019). \"Maldici\u00f3n\" peaked at number 21 on the [[Productores de M\u00fasica de Espa\u00f1a|PROMUSICAE]] chart and is certified gold in Spain for selling over 20,000 copies.<ref>{{Citation|last=M\u00fasica|first=El portal de|title=Maldici\u00f3n - Lola Indigo x Lalo Ebratt {{!}} EPDM|url=https://www.elportaldemusica.es/single/lola-indigo-x-lalo-ebratt-maldicion|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref> The single also charted in Colombia at number 80, marking the first single of Indigo to enter a musical chart outside Spain.\n\n== Background ==\nAfter relasing her second single \"Mujer Bruja\", Indigo began teasing her debut studio album and revealed that it would have a concept focused in witchery. On March 15, 2019, she announced that \"Akelarre\" would be released in April which didn't happen because of multiple delays due to disagreements with the record label. Through her respective social networks, Lola Indigo announced on April 20 that the third single from her new album \"Maldici\u00f3n\", in collaboration with Colombian rapper Lalo Ebratt, would be released on April 26 of that same year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vinilonegro.com/2019/04/lola-indigo-da-comienzo-la-cuenta-atras-para-akelarre-con-su-nueva-cancion-maldicion-que-se-lanza-el-26-de-abril/|title=Lola Indigo da comienzo la cuenta atr\u00e1s para \u2018Akelarre\u2019, con su nueva canci\u00f3n \u2018Maldici\u00f3n\u2019, que se lanza el 26 de abril|date=2019-04-19|website=Vinilo Negro|language=es|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref> \n\n== Music video ==\nThe music video for \"Maldici\u00f3n\" was released on April 26 and features both singers and multiple dancers jamming to the song. The videoclip features some dark scenarios, a recreation of Lucifer's throne and also shows Indigo blending the appearance of ''[[The Birth of Venus]]'' as painted by [[Sandro Botticelli]] in the 1480s decade.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cosmopolitan.com/es/famosos/musica/a27279716/lola-indigo-maldicion-nueva-cancion/|title=Nos hemos vuelto completamente 'malas' al escuchar la nueva canci\u00f3n de Lola Indigo: 'Maldici\u00f3n'|last=Panicello|first=Por Nerea|date=2019-04-26|website=Cosmopolitan|language=es-ES|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref> The music video received over one milion views in its first 24 hours and was the most-bought music video on ITunes Spain for a small amount of hours.\n\n== Live performances ==\nIndigo performed \"Maldici\u00f3n\" for the first time as part of her \"Indigo Tour\" on April 27, 2019, when she performed at the Dance Park Festival in Torrej\u00f3n de Ardoz. Indigo also performed the single and on other several festivals as well as on her Akelarre Tour, which run from May to November 2019 and is set to begin a festival extension in June 2020. The song was first performed on live television on May 16 at ''[[El Hormiguero]]'', Spain's main and most-watched late night show.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.antena3.com/programas/el-hormiguero/invitados/lola-indigo-y-su-ultimo-single-maldicion-cautivan-el-plato_201905165cddc8560cf27d3dafd39cc3.html|title=Lola \u00cdndigo y su \u00faltimo single 'Maldici\u00f3n' cautivan el plat\u00f3 de 'El Hormiguero 3.0'|date=2019-05-16|website=Antena3|language=es|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref> Indigo also sang the track at the [[Los 40|Los40 Primavera Pop]] shows in Barcelona and Madrid, with the last one being aired on ''[[Divinity (TV channel)|Divinity]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://los40.com/los40/2019/05/17/videos/1558117704_685276.html|title=Lola \u00cdndigo hace rugir al p\u00fablico con su actuaci\u00f3n en LOS40 Primavera Pop|last=LOS40|date=2019-05-18|website=LOS40|language=es|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n\n== Charts ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! scope=\"col\" |Chart (2019)\n! scope=\"col\" |Peak<br />position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |Spain ([[Productores de M\u00fasica de Espa\u00f1a|PROMUSICAE]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.elportaldemusica.es/lists/top-100-canciones/2019/18|title=El portal de M\u00fasica|website=www.elportaldemusica.es|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n|21\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |Colombia ([[National-Report]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190523143603/http://www.national-report.com/top-colombia/|title=Top 100 Colombia - national-REPORT|date=2019-05-23|website=web.archive.org|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n|80\n|}\n\n== Certifications ==\n{{Certification Table Top}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Spain|artist=Lola Indigo|title=Maldici\u00f3n|award=Gold|type=single|relyear=2019|certyear=2019|id=lola-indigo-lalo-ebratt-maldici\u00f3n|accessdate=14 April 2020}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom|nosales=true}}\n\n== Release history ==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n!Country\n!Date\n!Format\n!Label\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |Various\n|April 26, 2019\n|{{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[Streaming media|streaming]]}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Universal Music]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |Spain\n|April 28, 2019\n|[[Contemporary hit radio]]\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2019 singles]]\n[[Category:2019 songs]]\n", "name_user": "Arjayay", "label": "safe", "comment": "relase > release", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maldici%C3%B3n_(song)"}
{"title_page": "REICK (DJ)", "text_new": "'''[Koushik Mukherjee]''' known professionally as '''[REICK]''' ''(previously went by the stage name Koushik Mukherjee)'' is an [[Indian people|Indian]] [[Disc jockey|DJ]], songwriter and record producer based in [[Kolkata]], [[India]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/koushik-mukherjee-mn0003582679/discography|title=Koushik Mukherjee {{!}} Album Discography|website=AllMusic|language=en-us|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://open.spotify.com/artist/4DPP90htu1QIrbeZ6g3OAs|title=REICK|website=Spotify|language=en|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref> He is best known for his \n\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| background       = non_vocal_instrumentalist\n| image            = Reickshoot1.jpg\n| alias            = Koushik Mukherjee, DJ Koushik, REICK\n| birth_name       = Koushik Mukherjee\n| birth_place      = kolkata, India\n| caption          = REICK at The Westin Kolkata 2019\n| genre            = {{flatlist|\n* [[Trap music (EDM)|Trap]]\n* [[Electronic dance music|EDM]]\n* [[tropical house]] \n* [[French house]]\n* [[moombahton]]\n* [[dubstep]]\n* [[pop music|pop]]\n* [[Hip hop music|hip hop]]\n* [[House music|bass house]]\n}}\n| instrument       = {{flatlist|\n* Keyboards\n* piano\n* [[synthesizer]]\n}}\n| name             = REICK\n| occupation       = {{flatlist|\n* DJ\n* record producer\n}}\n| origin           = [[Kolkata]], India\n| years_active     = 2009\u2013present\n}}\n\nability to create an unique vibe while performing or producing music. Some of his most popular tracks are \"'''Slow Love'''\" featuring [[Jimmy Burney]] , \"'''There For You'''\" which did turn out to be an important mark to begin his career as a record producer.\n\n== Career ==\nREICK has performed across the country at various clubs, music festivals alongside some of the finest Indian and international artists.\n\nHe has began his career interning with [[The Thrillseekers]] which did help him gain interest and perfect his art for electronic music.\n\nHe made his first official release '''\"There For You\"''' as Koushik Mukherjee which peaked onto #52 rank on Top 100 Electronica charts at [[Beatport]]. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/there-for-you-mw0003010771|title=There for You - Koushik Mukherjee {{!}} Songs, Reviews, Credits|website=AllMusic|language=en-us|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.beatport.com/artist/koushik-mukherjee/580276|title=Koushik Mukherjee Tracks & Releases on Beatport|website=www.beatport.com|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n\nSuccess came in as he dropped his new single '''[https://fanlink.to/reickmusic \"Slow Love\"]''' under his new stage name '''REICK'''. Slow Love garnered alot of attention with it peaking onto #2 rank on [[ITunes Store|iTunes]] India Dance Charts and #91 on iTunes India charts <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kworb.net/itunes/artist/reick.html|title=REICK Chart Positions on iTunes/Spotify/YouTube|website=kworb.net|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref> within the first week of the release. Slow Love has over 1.1 Million views on [[YouTube (channel)|YouTube]]<ref>{{Citation|title=REICK ft. Jimmy Burney - Slow Love (Official Music Video)|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9hqVWE8QEA0|language=en|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref> , and is also being aired on [[VH1 India|Vh1]].\n\n== Discography ==\n\n=== '''Singles''' ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Title             \n!Year\n!Album\n!Notes\n|-\n|\"Himalaya\" \ncredited as a co producer\n\nfo inDjnous Tribe along with Dj Harish <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.beatport.com/track/himalaya-original-mix/4211508|title=Himalaya (Original Mix) by DJ Harish, Sid & Koushik, InDJnous Tribe on Beatport|website=www.beatport.com|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>    \n|2013  \n|Single \n|\n|-\n|\"There For You\"\ncredited as Koushik Mukherjee <ref>{{Citation|title=\u200eThere For You - Single by Koushik Mukherjee|url=https://music.apple.com/in/album/there-for-you-single/