ot More Murder|url=https://www.slashfilm.com/happy-death-day-trailer/|website=/Film|accessdate=16 June 2017|date=15 June 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Happy Death Day 2U]]'' || 2019 || Immediately after the events of the first film, Tree Gelbman ([[Jessica Rothe]]) unexpectedly re-enters the time loop and becomes determined to escape it after finding out her friends are now involved.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Ouelette|first1=Jennifer|title=A Pesky Time Loop Meets the Multiverse in Happy Death Day 2U First Trailer|url=https://arstechnica.com/gaming/2018/11/a-pesky-time-loop-meets-the-multiverse-in-happy-death-day-2us-first-trailer/|website=/Film|accessdate=1 December 2018|date=1 December 2018}}</ref><ref>url=https://screenrant.com/happy-death-day-2u-movie-reviews/</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Harry_Potter_and_the_Prisoner_of_Azkaban_(film)|Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban]]||2004||Harry and Hermione travel back in time and experience the same day from a different perspective. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.reddit.com/r/harrypotter/comments/19x7yr/an_explanation_of_harry_potter_time_travel_why/|title=r/harrypotter - An Explanation of Harry Potter Time Travel: Why Changing the Past is Really Changing the Future|website=reddit|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-13}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Haunter (film)|Haunter]]'' || 2013 || The ghost of a teenager, Lisa Johnson ([[Abigail Breslin]]) who, along with her family, keeps reliving the same day (although she is the only one aware of it) tries to protect a young girl, Olivia (Eleanor Zichy) and her family from a dead serial killer, the Pale Man ([[Stephen McHattie]]) who can possess the living.<ref>{{cite web|last=Rotten| first=Doc|title=Film Review: Haunter (2013)|url=https://horrornews.net/80348/film-review-haunter-2013|publisher=HorrorNews |accessdate=23 May 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Horse Girl]]''\n|2020\n|Sarah ([[Alison Brie]]) is a shy and awkward woman slowly losing touch with reality as she begins to believe that she is a clone of her grandmother. She loses time, [[Sleepwalking|sleepwalks]], and has disturbing dreams, which she believes is a product of an [[alien abduction]]. The movie ends with Sarah reliving the same week from a different perspective. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://screenrant.com/horse-girl-movie-ending-time-travel-explained/|title=Netflix's Horse Girl Ending Explained|date=2020-02-07|website=ScreenRant|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-13}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''Hurok'' || 2016 || A young drug dealer betrays his boss guy and later abandons his girlfriend, but finds himself caught up in a time loop.<ref>{{cite web|title=Loop: \"You\u2019re dead! What are you doing here?\"|url=https://cineuropa.org/en/newsdetail/324633/|website=cineuropa|accessdate=3 March 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[If Only (film)|If Only]]'' || 2004 || A man (Paul Nicholls) tries to avert destiny when he gets an opportunity to relive the day his lover (Jennifer Love Hewitt) died in an auto accident.<ref>[https://boxofficemojo.com/movies/intl/?page=&country=AR&id=_fIFONLY01 If Only on Box Office Mojo]</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[The Incident (2014 film)|The Incident]]'' || 2014 || Two stories of groups trapped in infinite time and space loops. One, and endless staircase, another and endless road, both looping back on themselves. While time resets in their surroundings each day, the trapped characters continue to age within the loops.<ref>[https://variety.com/2015/film/festivals/the-incident-review-isaac-ezban-1201616810/ Film Review: \u2018The Incident\u2019]</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[The Infinite Man (film)|The Infinite Man]]'' || 2014 || After a romantic weekend break with his girlfriend goes awry, a scientist invents time travel in order to create for her the perfect getaway, but inadvertently traps her in a recurring temporal loop.<ref>{{cite web|last=Hedone|title=Hedone / The Infinite Man|url=http://hedone.com.au/projects/the-infinite-man |accessdate=24 Feb 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[The Last Day of Summer (2007 film)|The Last Day of Summer]]'' |